<Data CreatedBy="admin" CreatedOn="634129091169427609" UpdatedBy="admin" UpdatedOn="634129092140540004">
  <Properties />
  <Nodes>
    <Header Code="HeaderElement1" Type="Subtitle" ShowInTOC="0"><![CDATA[The example]]></Header>
    <Paragraph Code="ParagraphElement1"><![CDATA[<p>The demonstrated TableLayoutPanel contains panels with the following values:<br />Red panel: Column=0, Row=0, ColumnSpan=2 and RowSpan=1.<br />Yellow panel: Column=2, Row=0, ColumnSpan=1 and RowSpan=2.</p>]]></Paragraph>
    <Header Code="HeaderElement2" Type="Subtitle" ShowInTOC="0"><![CDATA[General Info]]></Header>
    <Paragraph Code="ParagraphElement2"><![CDATA[<p>The Visual WebGui <em>TableLayoutPanel </em>represents a panel that dynamically lays out its contents in a grid composed of rows and columns. The <em>TableLayoutPanel </em>control adds the following properties to its child controls: <em>Cell</em>, <em>Column</em>, <em>Row</em>, <em>ColumnSpan</em>, and <em>RowSpan</em>. You can manipulate with the positions of child control and merge its cells by setting appropriate properties. </p>]]></Paragraph>
  </Nodes>
</Data>
